But, Ghebreab disagreed, saying the government has implemented measures to meet the UN‚Äôs efforts to improve living standards and alleviating poverty. This, he says, in spite of sanctions imposed on the country.
‚ÄúEritrea has made huge strides over the past two decades. We are on track in meeting most of the UN Millennium Development Goals. The Eritrean government takes care of its youth and creates opportunities for them,‚Äù said Ghebreab. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs just not Eritreans, its Africans in general that are trying to migrate to Europe and other places.‚Äù
